=== Etymology ===
From Greek ''mesos'' &ndash; between, and ''potos'' &ndash; river, the area between the rivers.

=== Proper Noun ===
'''Mesopotamia'''

#a region in Southwest [[Asia]] spanning from the mountains between the [[Euphrates]] and [[Tigris]] rivers, from the mountains of East [[Asia Minor]] to the [[Persian Gulf]]
# all of the Euphrates-Tigris valley
# the ancient cultures that were once present in Mesopotamia

